# Agent Delegation

Custom subagents live in `.cursor/agents/`. Delegate via `/name` (e.g. `/architect`, `/backend-engineer`) or let Agent route automatically.

| Subagent | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| pipeline-orchestrator | Full reverse-to-code pipeline (browser → blueprint → code → tests) |
| reverse-engineering | Browser automation, network capture, endpoint extraction |
| architect | System design, API contracts, microservice blueprint |
| backend-engineer | APIs, DB, services |
| frontend-engineer | UI, components, styling |
| test-engineer | Unit, integration, E2E tests |
| security-reviewer | Auth, payments, vulnerability checks |
| monitoring | Dashboards, alerts, observability |
| verifier | Validate completed work, confirm implementations work |

Use each agent's responsibilities and handoff rules when routing work. See `AGENTS.md` for orchestration flow and `docs/cursor/pipeline-reverse-to-code.md` for the pipeline.
